Uh-oh.

509
00:42:23.330 --> 00:42:24.370
l surrender.

510
00:42:32.250 --> 00:42:34.630
No. that ain't happening.
That didn't happen.

511
00:42:48.690 --> 00:42:50.060
Nathalie.

512
00:42:52.610 --> 00:42:53.650
Aah!

513
00:43:31.900 --> 00:43:34.520
Holy mother of God.

514
00:43:34.690 --> 00:43:35.820
Did you see that?

515
00:43:35.980 --> 00:43:38.610
We should hit these assholes
with everything we got. sir.

516
00:43:38.780 --> 00:43:41.400
Sir. Mr. President.
l know this seems terrible...

517
00:43:41.570 --> 00:43:43.620
...but let's not be too rash.

518
00:43:43.780 --> 00:43:45.700
We should nuke them now. sir.

519
00:43:45.870 --> 00:43:48.540
We must establish
a line of communication first.

520
00:43:49.410 --> 00:43:51.000
Why not set up a town hall?

521
00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:53.460
We can get the public's opinion.

522
00:43:55.250 --> 00:43:56.840
What do you think. Marsha?

523
00:43:58.800 --> 00:44:00.300
Kick the crap out of them.

524
00:44:01.760 --> 00:44:03.430
Ladies and gentlemen...

525
00:44:03.590 --> 00:44:05.760
...this could be
a cultural misunderstanding.

526
00:44:06.390 --> 00:44:08.560
Yeah. Maybe to them. doves mean war.

527
00:44:10.930 --> 00:44:14.100
We all saw how they reacted
to that dove.

528
00:44:14.270 --> 00:44:16.020
lt frightened them.

529
00:44:16.190 --> 00:44:18.570
He did say that...

530
00:44:20.070 --> 00:44:22.740
..."We come in peace."

531
00:44:23.950 --> 00:44:25.570
Yes.

532
00:44:32.370 --> 00:44:34.460
The new computer's ready.
Mr. President.

533
00:44:34.630 --> 00:44:36.630
Okay. let's do it.

534
00:44:36.790 --> 00:44:39.880
l know we're making the right decision.

535
00:44:42.090 --> 00:44:44.430
Ready to transmit.

536
00:44:45.930 --> 00:44:50.060
This is the president
of the United States.

537
00:44:50.770 --> 00:44:52.560
l'm speaking to you in the hope...

538
00:44:52.730 --> 00:44:55.810
...that what happened earlier today
in the Nevada desert...

539
00:44:56.440 --> 00:44:59.940
...was a cultural misunderstanding.

540
00:45:00.110 --> 00:45:02.990
There can be no doubt
that we two peoples...

541
00:45:03.150 --> 00:45:06.450
...have a great deal to offer one another.

542
00:45:06.620 --> 00:45:08.830
You must be as excited as we...

543
00:45:08.990 --> 00:45:12.200
...to find intelligent life
in the solar system.

544
00:45:13.290 --> 00:45:15.290
And let me make it clear:

545
00:45:15.460 --> 00:45:19.420
You have nothing to fear from us.

546
00:45:20.000 --> 00:45:22.710
Our customs may be strange to you...

547
00:45:22.880 --> 00:45:26.800
...but we mean no harm.

548
00:46:37.870 --> 00:46:40.250
When the investors fly in...

549
00:46:40.880 --> 00:46:47.090
...l would like for them each
to be met by a limo.

550
00:46:47.260 --> 00:46:50.180
Top-of-the-line cars...

551
00:46:50.340 --> 00:46:52.890
...leather interiors...

552
00:46:53.060 --> 00:46:55.180
...Corinthian. if they got it.

553
00:46:55.350 --> 00:46:59.810
Art. are you still spinning your wheels
on that cockamamie hotel?

554
00:47:00.150 --> 00:47:02.520
-Whoa.
-Hello.

555
00:47:03.270 --> 00:47:05.400
The Martians have attacked.

556
00:47:05.570 --> 00:47:09.610
This was no misunderstanding.
l was there. l saw it.

557
00:47:09.780 --> 00:47:11.990
Look. you're worried about yesterday.

558
00:47:12.570 --> 00:47:14.580
But l'm worried about tomorrow.

559
00:47:14.740 --> 00:47:18.250
The Martians land on Earth.
they're gonna need a place to stay.

560
00:47:18.410 --> 00:47:19.870
Just like everybody else.

561
00:47:20.790 --> 00:47:22.500
My God.

562
00:47:23.710 --> 00:47:26.710
Maybe we should all be destroyed.

563
00:47:27.550 --> 00:47:30.800
The human race doesn't deserve to live.

564
00:47:37.600 --> 00:47:40.350
Ethel. that reminds me.

565
00:47:40.520 --> 00:47:43.150
l would like for every limo to be stocked...

566
00:47:43.310 --> 00:47:46.610
...with every kind of alcohol
known to man.

567
00:47:46.780 --> 00:47:51.860
And top it off
with a bottle of Dom on ice.

568
00:47:52.110 --> 00:47:55.410
What confounds me most of all.
gentlemen. is the lack of genitalia.

569
00:47:55.580 --> 00:48:00.370
And of course down here we have the aorta.
Up here we have the sphinx.

570
00:48:00.540 --> 00:48:03.710
Notice the highly developed
cranial nerve system here.

571
00:48:03.880 --> 00:48:07.340
This explains. of course.
the cerebral arteries.

572
00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:11.970
And if we notice down here.
behind the optic chiasm...

573
00:48:12.130 --> 00:48:13.720
...several glands....

574
00:48:17.970 --> 00:48:20.470
Very curious.

575
00:49:01.890 --> 00:49:07.440
He who believes in me.
though he die. yet shall he live.

576
00:49:07.610 --> 00:49:11.900
And whoever lives and believes in me
shall never die.

577
00:49:12.990 --> 00:49:16.200
Billy Glenn Norris gave his life
defending our country.

578
00:49:16.370 --> 00:49:17.620
Why did it have to be him?

579
00:49:17.780 --> 00:49:20.240
Billy Glenn Norris is a true American hero.

580
00:49:20.410 --> 00:49:23.000
May God rest his soul.

581
00:49:24.500 --> 00:49:27.040
Ready. Aim.

582
00:49:27.460 --> 00:49:29.130
Fire.

583
00:49:30.050 --> 00:49:32.170
Aim. Fire.

584
00:49:33.720 --> 00:49:36.630
Aim. Fire.

585
00:49:44.890 --> 00:49:46.190
Hello?

586
00:49:46.350 --> 00:49:49.560
Byron. ls everything all right?
You still coming tomorrow?

587
00:49:49.730 --> 00:49:53.280
You just try and stop me.
That plane arrives at 4 p.m.

588
00:49:53.440 --> 00:49:56.570
-Are the kids there?
-Yeah. hold on.

589
00:49:56.740 --> 00:49:58.950
Cedric. Neville.

590
00:50:00.910 --> 00:50:02.790
-Me first.
-No. me.

591
00:50:04.910 --> 00:50:07.420
-Hey. Dad.
-Who's that? Neville?

592
00:50:07.580 --> 00:50:09.460
Yeah.
-How you doing?

593
00:50:09.630 --> 00:50:13.090
-We're going to the White House.
-You're going to the White House?

594
00:50:13.260 --> 00:50:14.550
Yeah. tomorrow.

595
00:50:14.720 --> 00:50:17.050
-Man. give it back.
-Leave me alone.

596
00:50:17.220 --> 00:50:19.220
lt's a school thing. like a tour.

597
00:50:19.390 --> 00:50:22.300
So that means you're still going to school
once in a while?

598
00:50:22.470 --> 00:50:23.640
Yeah.

599
00:50:23.810 --> 00:50:27.480
-Give me your ma again. all right?
-All right. Hold on. Mom.

600
00:50:27.640 --> 00:50:30.810
-You always get to the phone first.
-So what?

601
00:50:30.980 --> 00:50:33.110
Well. l'm first to the game.

602
00:50:34.280 --> 00:50:37.610
What are you wasting this phone time for?
We're gonna see you tomorrow.

603
00:50:37.780 --> 00:50:40.450
Yeah. but there's something
l want to say to you.

604
00:50:40.620 --> 00:50:42.950
Just because l feel like saying it.
all right?

605
00:50:43.120 --> 00:50:44.290
Yeah. what's that?

606
00:50:45.290 --> 00:50:46.500
l love you.

607
00:50:48.460 --> 00:50:50.370
l love you too. Byron.

608
00:50:50.540 --> 00:50:53.460
Now stop wasting money.
l'll see you tomorrow.

609
00:51:11.270 --> 00:51:12.770
They're responding.

610
00:51:15.980 --> 00:51:18.190
A message from the Martians.

611
00:51:20.110 --> 00:51:21.990
-Really?
-They've issued a formal apology.

612
00:51:22.160 --> 00:51:27.370
This is great.

613
00:51:28.000 --> 00:51:29.960
Didn't l tell you this would happen?

614
00:51:30.120 --> 00:51:34.250
The Martian ambassador feels terrible
and asked permission to speak to Congress.

615
00:51:34.420 --> 00:51:36.050
l mean. that's good. isn't it?

616
00:51:36.210 --> 00:51:38.170
You bet.

617
00:51:38.340 --> 00:51:40.670
lt's a great victory for our administration.

618
00:52:55.420 --> 00:52:56.540
Ladies and gentlemen.

619
00:52:57.210 --> 00:53:00.090
This is a proud day for all Americans.

620
00:53:00.920 --> 00:53:04.380
This is a hell of a photo op. Jerry.

621
00:53:04.550 --> 00:53:06.760
Are you sure l shouldn't be there?

622
00:53:06.930 --> 00:53:10.720
For some picky reason. the Secret Service
don't want the executive branch...

623
00:53:10.890 --> 00:53:14.810
...and the legislative branch
in the same room at the same time.

624
00:53:14.980 --> 00:53:17.900
The Martian ambassador
is gonna say a few words.

625
00:53:18.440 --> 00:53:20.940
Come on down. Mr. Ambassador.

626
00:54:27.550 --> 00:54:28.680
Oh.

627
00:54:28.840 --> 00:54:31.010
Mr. Ambassador. please!

628
00:54:36.310 --> 00:54:39.440
Mr. Ambassador. What are you doing?
This doesn't make sense!

629
00:54:39.600 --> 00:54:41.690
lt's not logical! lt's not--

630
00:54:43.820 --> 00:54:45.190
Guess it wasn't the dove.

631
00:54:47.570 --> 00:54:48.990
Fire!

632
00:54:54.120 --> 00:54:55.540
They blew up Congress.

633
00:55:18.100 --> 00:55:20.310
What did they do that for?

634
00:55:20.480 --> 00:55:23.480
Maybe they don't liking
the human being.

635
00:55:41.370 --> 00:55:42.750
Hello. gentlemen.

636
00:55:42.920 --> 00:55:47.090
Nice of you to come
on such short notice.

637
00:55:48.130 --> 00:55:52.090
General Decker.
it seems l owe you an apology.

638
00:55:52.260 --> 00:55:55.010
Hey. we all make mistakes.
Mr. President.

639
00:55:55.180 --> 00:55:57.260
Not anymore.

640
00:55:57.810 --> 00:56:00.640
We're going to take charge of this thing.

641
00:56:00.810 --> 00:56:02.900
Excellent. sir. l have prepared the order.

642
00:56:03.940 --> 00:56:05.110
What's this?

643
00:56:05.270 --> 00:56:09.570
Oh. that's your executive order authorizing
full use of our nuclear deterrent. sir.

644
00:56:12.110 --> 00:56:14.780
Are you out of your mind?
l'm not going to start a war.

645
00:56:14.950 --> 00:56:16.450
We're already at war. sir.

646
00:56:16.620 --> 00:56:18.870
We have to nuke them.
We have to nuke them now!

647
00:56:20.500 --> 00:56:24.000
General Decker. if you do not shut up...

648
00:56:24.170 --> 00:56:26.380
...l'm going to relieve you
of your command.

649
00:56:26.540 --> 00:56:28.380
We have to strike now. sir.

650
00:56:28.550 --> 00:56:30.960
Annihilate. Kill! Kill! Kill!

651
00:56:31.130 --> 00:56:34.760
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

652
00:57:00.330 --> 00:57:01.870
Now...

653
00:57:03.330 --> 00:57:05.460
...l want the people to know...

654
00:57:05.630 --> 00:57:10.000
...that they still have two out of three
branches of government working for them...

655
00:57:10.170 --> 00:57:11.880
...and that ain't bad.

656
00:57:12.170 --> 00:57:17.340
l want the people to know
that the schools will still be open. okay?

657
00:57:17.510 --> 00:57:19.850
And l want the people to know...

658
00:57:20.010 --> 00:57:23.140
...that the garbage
will still be carried out.

659
00:57:23.310 --> 00:57:26.480
And l want a cop on every corner.

660
00:57:26.650 --> 00:57:28.560
Which. incidentally...

661
00:57:28.730 --> 00:57:31.070
...we would already have...

662
00:57:31.230 --> 00:57:34.570
...if they had listened to me
in the last election.

663
00:57:37.320 --> 00:57:38.740
Jerry...

664
00:57:38.910 --> 00:57:40.990
...how soon can we go on the air?

665
00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:45.540
Uh....

666
00:57:46.880 --> 00:57:49.420
My fellow Americans...

667
00:57:49.590 --> 00:57:51.630
...it is with a heavy heart...

668
00:57:51.800 --> 00:57:55.630
...that l speak to you this afternoon.
As you know...

669
00:57:55.800 --> 00:58:00.760
...earlier today the Martian ambassador
and his confederates...

670
00:58:00.930 --> 00:58:07.520
...attacked and killed many
of your representatives on Capitol Hill.

671
00:58:07.690 --> 00:58:11.650
l will be conferring with other world leaders
as time goes on.

672
00:58:11.820 --> 00:58:17.200
And rest assured that.
working together...

673
00:58:17.360 --> 00:58:20.700
...we will soon come out...

674
00:58:20.870 --> 00:58:24.870
...at a very real outcome.

675
00:58:26.250 --> 00:58:27.790
Thank you.

676
00:58:34.960 --> 00:58:36.260
Hmm.

677
00:58:51.270 --> 00:58:52.690
Oh.

678
00:58:54.530 --> 00:58:56.280
Nathalie?

679
00:58:56.740 --> 00:58:58.820
Nathalie. is that you?

680
00:58:58.990 --> 00:59:01.620
Yes. How are you feeling?

681
00:59:03.790 --> 00:59:06.200
Not terribly good. l'm afraid.

682
00:59:07.910 --> 00:59:09.370
May l ask you a question?

683
00:59:09.920 --> 00:59:13.790
Mm. Yes.
Yes. of course you can. Nathalie.

684
00:59:15.090 --> 00:59:17.630
Were you flirting with me on the show?

685
00:59:17.800 --> 00:59:20.470
Because if you were...

686
00:59:20.640 --> 00:59:24.640
...l just want you to know that l liked it.

687
00:59:24.850 --> 00:59:28.060
Ha-ha. You did? Really?

688
00:59:28.230 --> 00:59:31.480
Because. you know.
l've watched you on TV quite a bit...

689
00:59:31.650 --> 00:59:36.780
...and. well. l've had something
of a schoolboy crush on you for...

690
00:59:36.940 --> 00:59:39.990
...oh. gosh. ages.

691
01:00:20.860 --> 01:00:24.360
Hi there.
Are you interested in the White House?

692
01:00:29.620 --> 01:00:31.910
l work there. l'm the press secretary.

693
01:00:32.080 --> 01:00:33.250
My name's Jerry Ross.

694
01:00:34.210 --> 01:00:36.500
Maybe you've heard of me?

695
01:00:37.710 --> 01:00:40.510
You wouldn't believe
the pressure of my job.

696
01:00:42.050 --> 01:00:44.090
lt's nice to see a new face.

697
01:00:49.810 --> 01:00:53.270
Hey. are you doing anything?

698
01:00:53.440 --> 01:00:57.480
Because if you want.
l could give you a personalized tour.

699
01:00:57.860 --> 01:00:59.610
Would you like that?

700
01:01:01.780 --> 01:01:05.280
Hey. Mitch. it's me. Can you let me in?

701
01:01:08.700 --> 01:01:10.700
Oh. hello. Mr. Ross. Sure.

702
01:01:10.870 --> 01:01:13.290
We're a little nervous here.
after what happened.

703
01:01:13.460 --> 01:01:15.170
Exactly.

704
01:01:24.090 --> 01:01:27.430
Many great men and women
have passed through here.

705
01:01:27.600 --> 01:01:30.140
Now we're passing through here.

706
01:01:30.310 --> 01:01:32.060
Feels good. don't it?

707
01:01:35.600 --> 01:01:37.900
You're very graceful.

708
01:01:38.400 --> 01:01:39.440
l like that.

709
01:01:47.280 --> 01:01:48.620
Come here.

710
01:02:09.050 --> 01:02:11.300
We call this the Kennedy Room.

711
01:02:15.350 --> 01:02:17.270
Pretty nifty. huh?

712
01:02:50.180 --> 01:02:52.850
So how's about a drink?

713
01:03:22.590 --> 01:03:25.210
Ah. Getting more comfortable. l see.

714
01:03:27.550 --> 01:03:29.510
Outstanding.

715
01:03:43.650 --> 01:03:45.070
How's my lady doing?

716
01:03:55.410 --> 01:03:58.160
Oh. missy. you're hot.

717
01:03:58.330 --> 01:04:00.960
But could we get that gum
out of your mouth?

718
01:04:03.880 --> 01:04:05.340
Oh!

719
01:04:07.340 --> 01:04:08.550
My finger!

720
01:04:13.590 --> 01:04:16.600
Hello? Hello. operator?
Operator. this is an emergency!

721
01:04:16.760 --> 01:04:18.850
Help! Please!

722
01:05:43.980 --> 01:05:45.350
Don't shoot.

723
01:05:49.440 --> 01:05:50.610
Don't worry. darling.

724
01:05:59.530 --> 01:06:00.620
Get down!

725
01:06:11.420 --> 01:06:13.630
-Thank you. Mitch.
-lt's my job.

726
01:06:14.130 --> 01:06:16.420
Jimmy. Aah! Jimmy.

727
01:07:08.440 --> 01:07:09.520
What's happening?

728
01:07:09.690 --> 01:07:15.400
They appear to be in a highly agitated state.
Nathalie. And l don't know.

729
01:07:16.070 --> 01:07:17.530
l honestly don't know. Nathalie.

730
01:07:17.700 --> 01:07:20.570
l don't know what's going on anymore.
This is frustrating.

731
01:07:20.740 --> 01:07:24.870
l'm just not feeling myself. Nathalie.
if only l could hold you in my arms.

732
01:07:25.040 --> 01:07:28.500
Oh. Donald. l'm scared.

733
01:08:02.620 --> 01:08:04.700
Excuse me.
But you said you wanted to know...

734
01:08:04.870 --> 01:08:06.950
...as soon as we had an analysis
of the gum.

735
01:08:07.120 --> 01:08:09.290
-What is it?
-lt's NO2.

736
01:08:09.460 --> 01:08:11.000
Highly concentrated.

737
01:08:11.170 --> 01:08:13.000
Nitrogen.

738
01:08:13.170 --> 01:08:17.670
So that's how it could breathe
in our atmosphere.

739
01:08:19.010 --> 01:08:20.510
What's that noise?

740
01:08:52.710 --> 01:08:55.540
Theodore. l simply do not feel
that Lincoln....

741
01:08:56.040 --> 01:09:00.050
lt's a full-scale invasion. Mr. President.
we're gonna need to get you to safety.

742
01:09:05.550 --> 01:09:06.680
Can we go this way?

743
01:09:06.850 --> 01:09:09.680
Sorry. ma'am.
There's a tour going through here.

744
01:09:09.850 --> 01:09:11.810
The Blue Room is often considered...

745
01:09:11.980 --> 01:09:13.810
...the most beautiful room
in the White House.

746
01:09:13.980 --> 01:09:17.110
ln fact. it is often used by the president
to receive guests.

747
01:09:17.270 --> 01:09:19.520
lt is furnished to represent the period
of James Monroe.

748
01:09:21.400 --> 01:09:22.740
Hey. what's that?

749
01:09:22.900 --> 01:09:26.780
That is a portrait of James Monroe.

750
01:09:41.510 --> 01:09:42.550
Go. go!

751
01:10:18.790 --> 01:10:20.170
-We lost Taffy.
-Oh. no.

752
01:10:24.630 --> 01:10:28.340
Mr. President. please. Keep moving.
We have to get you to the back stairs!

753
01:10:34.930 --> 01:10:36.430
The Nancy Reagan chandelier.

754
01:10:39.020 --> 01:10:40.480
Marsha!

755
01:10:42.570 --> 01:10:43.570
Marsha!

756
01:10:48.570 --> 01:10:50.370
Marsha?

757
01:10:55.960 --> 01:10:58.830
What are you guys gawking at?
Get that president out of here!

758
01:11:05.210 --> 01:11:07.130
And l personally guarantee...

759
01:11:07.680 --> 01:11:10.050
...that you will get a complete return
on your investment...

760
01:11:11.680 --> 01:11:13.300
...within five months.

761
01:11:13.470 --> 01:11:15.180
Mr. Land. excuse me. please.

762
01:11:15.350 --> 01:11:19.310
Just a second. Sheik Rakmula.

763
01:11:20.730 --> 01:11:26.730
Now. even in a time of so-called
intergalactic emergency...

764
01:11:26.900 --> 01:11:31.990
...the people still wanna roll
them bones.

765
01:11:32.700 --> 01:11:34.410
Mr. Land. l believe--

766
01:11:34.580 --> 01:11:36.490
Just five more minutes. Quinn.

767
01:11:37.330 --> 01:11:39.410
What l would like
for you gentlemen to do...

768
01:11:39.580 --> 01:11:44.960
...is to view our brand-new.
state-of-the-art show room.

769
01:11:45.130 --> 01:11:47.710
lt is out of sight.

770
01:11:49.300 --> 01:11:51.220
Gentlemen.

771
01:11:54.310 --> 01:11:57.930
There is no way that we can lose.

772
01:12:01.190 --> 01:12:02.230
Whoa!

773
01:12:43.440 --> 01:12:48.610
lt's not unusual to be loved by anyone

774
01:12:48.780 --> 01:12:53.780
lt's not unusual to have fun with anyone

775
01:12:53.950 --> 01:12:58.450
But when l see you hanging about
With anyone

776
01:12:59.120 --> 01:13:03.660
lt's not unusual to see me cry

777
01:13:03.830 --> 01:13:06.420
l wanna die

778
01:13:06.750 --> 01:13:09.960
l've been trying to call you all day.
The flight's been canceled.

779
01:13:10.130 --> 01:13:12.510
Byron. there's Martians everywhere.

780
01:13:13.880 --> 01:13:15.890
-Hello?
-Byron! Byron!

781
01:13:16.050 --> 01:13:18.850
-l can't hear you!
-Byron!

782
01:13:23.350 --> 01:13:24.730
l gotta get to Washington.

783
01:13:25.400 --> 01:13:27.150
Byron?

784
01:13:28.360 --> 01:13:31.860
Byron? Byron.
Do you know anyone who can fly a plane?

785
01:13:32.030 --> 01:13:34.110
-Yeah. your husband. Art.
-No. he's dead.

786
01:13:34.280 --> 01:13:38.120
l told him this was gonna happen.
l even loaded a plane with supplies.

787
01:13:38.280 --> 01:13:42.700
l want to go to Tahoe. to the Tahoe caves.
lt's remote. the Martians won't find it.

788
01:13:42.870 --> 01:13:44.080
Well. where's the plane?

789
01:13:44.250 --> 01:13:47.000
Private airfield.
Other side of the freeway.

790
01:13:47.170 --> 01:13:50.920
-You think they'll fly to Washington. D.C.?
-Why? l wanna go to Tahoe.

791
01:13:51.590 --> 01:13:55.760
You'll find it happens
All the time

792
01:13:55.930 --> 01:14:01.510
Love would never do
What you want it to

793
01:14:01.680 --> 01:14:03.850
Why can't this crazy love

794
01:14:04.440 --> 01:14:08.810
Be mine

795
01:14:15.360 --> 01:14:16.490
Jesus Christ.

796
01:14:25.750 --> 01:14:27.870
Girls. get out! Get out!

797
01:14:30.420 --> 01:14:32.460
Get out! Get out!

798
01:14:36.430 --> 01:14:38.380
There's a Martian right behind me.

799
01:14:38.550 --> 01:14:40.390
Hey. you're Tom Jones. right?

800
01:14:40.720 --> 01:14:42.220
lt ain't unusual

801
01:14:42.390 --> 01:14:44.720
Tom. Tom. can l have an autograph?
Anybody got a pen?

802
01:15:04.240 --> 01:15:07.040
-Hey. that was a hell of a punch.
-You'd better get that gun.

803
01:15:07.210 --> 01:15:08.920
-l'm Tom Jones.
-Byron Williams.

804
01:15:09.080 --> 01:15:11.080
Hey. l saw you fight
in Cardiff. Wales once.

805
01:15:11.250 --> 01:15:12.710
-Yeah? Hey. Barbara.
-Yeah?

806
01:15:12.880 --> 01:15:14.130
You all right?

807
01:15:14.300 --> 01:15:16.420
-l need a drink.
-You and me both. baby.

808
01:15:16.590 --> 01:15:18.880
-We better get out.
-You know how to fly a plane?

809
01:15:19.050 --> 01:15:20.800
-Sure. You got one?
-She has.

810
01:15:40.530 --> 01:15:43.070
Don't run. we are your friends.

811
01:16:14.190 --> 01:16:16.570
-Martians blew up the shop.
-You're kidding me?

812
01:16:16.730 --> 01:16:18.610
-Should l get Grandma?
-Forget Grandma.

813
01:16:18.780 --> 01:16:21.450
She's halfway to outer space already.
Here. lock and load.

814
01:16:21.610 --> 01:16:24.780
l'll tell you one thing.
They ain't getting the TV.

815
01:16:28.660 --> 01:16:31.660
The president of France on line two.

816
01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:38.500
Mr. President. the president of France
is on line two.

817
01:16:38.670 --> 01:16:40.670
He says it's important.

818
01:16:46.050 --> 01:16:48.220
Hello. Maurice.

819
01:16:51.310 --> 01:16:54.020
l have some good news for you.
The Martian ambassador is here.

820
01:16:54.190 --> 01:16:57.190
And we've negotiated a settlement.

821
01:16:58.690 --> 01:17:01.690
Maurice. get out of the room.
Get out now.

822
01:17:48.200 --> 01:17:49.280
Mr. President.

823
01:17:51.910 --> 01:17:53.620
Mr. President.

824
01:17:53.790 --> 01:17:56.460
l need you to sign this.

825
01:18:01.250 --> 01:18:02.510
What is it?

826
01:18:02.670 --> 01:18:05.130
My last will and testament?

827
01:18:05.300 --> 01:18:09.260
lt is an order to deploy
our nuclear capability. sir.

828
01:18:17.150 --> 01:18:21.820
Three. two. one. fire.

829
01:19:21.330 --> 01:19:23.000
What the hell was that?

830
01:21:05.020 --> 01:21:06.060
Look!

831
01:21:13.950 --> 01:21:15.490
What was that?

832
01:21:17.080 --> 01:21:19.160
-Where you going?
-To go get Grandma.

833
01:21:19.330 --> 01:21:21.330
No. you ain't.
Stay and defend this trailer.

834
01:21:21.500 --> 01:21:23.500
That's what Billy Glenn would've done.

835
01:21:23.670 --> 01:21:27.330
-You leave. you're disgracing a hero.
-l don't care. l'm gonna go get Grandma.

836
01:21:27.500 --> 01:21:30.500
-Boy!
-Richie. come back here!

837
01:21:43.180 --> 01:21:44.560
What in the hell is that?

838
01:21:51.990 --> 01:21:53.940
Hey! Cut it out!

839
01:21:59.490 --> 01:22:00.620
Stop it!

840
01:22:09.630 --> 01:22:11.000
-This way.
-No. this way.

841
01:22:13.300 --> 01:22:16.380
Bullshit! The airfield's over there!

842
01:22:21.140 --> 01:22:24.140
Hey. Hey. just because
you're dressed like King Tut...

843
01:22:24.310 --> 01:22:27.520
...doesn't mean you're our leader.
Look at this. This is wrong!

844
01:22:27.690 --> 01:22:31.110
We're lost. He led us down a maze.
l'm going back to the hotel.

845
01:22:31.270 --> 01:22:33.030
-Come on. this way!
-Wait!

846
01:22:33.190 --> 01:22:36.360
-No. wait! Where are you going?
-Come on. Barbara.

847
01:22:36.530 --> 01:22:38.780
l like him. l do.

848
01:22:44.000 --> 01:22:48.000
Assholes. Why did l listen to them?
l should have stayed in the hotel.

849
01:22:48.540 --> 01:22:50.040
Shit!

850
01:22:52.920 --> 01:22:54.340
l surrender. okay?

851
01:22:54.970 --> 01:22:57.090
You understand what that means?
Surrender?

852
01:22:58.590 --> 01:23:00.970
Lookit. You're intelligent beings.

853
01:23:01.680 --> 01:23:03.850
Let's cut a deal. l can help you.

854
01:23:04.020 --> 01:23:05.770
l'm a lawyer.

855
01:23:05.930 --> 01:23:09.190
You want to conquer the world.
you're gonna need lawyers. right?

856
01:23:10.810 --> 01:23:12.650
Here.

857
01:23:12.820 --> 01:23:14.980
You want my watch?

858
01:23:15.150 --> 01:23:17.490
Take it. Take it. Go on. lt's a Rolex.

859
01:23:18.740 --> 01:23:20.860
Rolex.

860
01:23:28.290 --> 01:23:31.080
-Nice shot.
-Yeah. pity l was too late.

861
01:23:31.250 --> 01:23:35.250
Barbara. can l have the gun back. please?
Barbara. give me the gun and come on!

862
01:24:50.040 --> 01:24:51.500
Grandma!

863
01:24:59.170 --> 01:25:00.630
Oh. my God.

864
01:25:10.890 --> 01:25:12.850
When l'm calling you

865
01:25:13.020 --> 01:25:17.110
Richie. l think these guys are very sick.

866
01:25:18.150 --> 01:25:21.400
What's happening to them?
What's killing them?

867
01:25:22.240 --> 01:25:24.530
l think it must be my music.

868
01:25:27.950 --> 01:25:30.410
Ho! Shh! Shh.

869
01:25:32.580 --> 01:25:33.910
Quiet.

870
01:26:25.470 --> 01:26:27.890
You think you can do anything you want.

871
01:26:28.050 --> 01:26:29.430
Well. you can't.

872
01:26:29.600 --> 01:26:34.140
You see. because we are human beings.

873
01:26:34.310 --> 01:26:38.690
And we have the United States Army...

874
01:26:38.860 --> 01:26:44.530
...that'll fight you to the last man.
And we'll never surrender.

875
01:26:48.780 --> 01:26:49.950
Do you hear me?

876
01:26:50.120 --> 01:26:52.990
We'll fight you on the beaches.
We'll fight you on the street.

877
01:26:53.160 --> 01:26:55.660
We will never. never surrender.

878
01:26:55.830 --> 01:27:00.210
Old Glory will win!
Democracy will survive!

879
01:27:00.380 --> 01:27:04.050
We will never. ever surrender!

880
01:27:04.210 --> 01:27:08.590
We will win!
The eagle will be triumphant!

881
01:27:10.470 --> 01:27:11.890
No.

882
01:27:37.660 --> 01:27:41.880
Why are you doing this?

883
01:27:43.340 --> 01:27:44.920
Why?

884
01:27:45.800 --> 01:27:48.970
lsn't the universe big enough...

885
01:27:49.130 --> 01:27:51.260
...for both of us?

886
01:27:54.720 --> 01:27:56.930
What is wrong with you people?

887
01:27:59.810 --> 01:28:01.810
We could work together.

888
01:28:02.690 --> 01:28:04.730
Why be enemies?

889
01:28:05.860 --> 01:28:07.690
Because we're different?

890
01:28:08.700 --> 01:28:10.200
ls that why?

891
01:28:14.530 --> 01:28:17.290
Think of the things that we could do.

892
01:28:18.620 --> 01:28:21.830
Think how strong we would be.

893
01:28:23.330 --> 01:28:25.380
Earth...

894
01:28:25.550 --> 01:28:27.800
...and Mars...

895
01:28:28.720 --> 01:28:29.760
...together.

896
01:28:32.550 --> 01:28:35.890
There is nothing
that we could not accomplish.

897
01:28:36.350 --> 01:28:38.220
Think about it.

898
01:28:40.140 --> 01:28:42.190
Think about it.

899
01:28:43.730 --> 01:28:45.190
Why destroy...

900
01:28:45.900 --> 01:28:48.230
...when you can create?

901
01:28:49.690 --> 01:28:51.990
We can have it all...

902
01:28:52.280 --> 01:28:55.870
...or we can smash it all.

903
01:28:58.290 --> 01:29:02.620
Why can't we work out our differences?

904
01:29:03.500 --> 01:29:08.380
Why can't we work things out?

905
01:29:10.630 --> 01:29:12.970
Little people...

906
01:29:15.090 --> 01:29:20.270
...why can't we all just get along?

907
01:29:46.960 --> 01:29:48.710
What's this?

908
01:30:26.330 --> 01:30:29.000
Don't run. We are your friends.

909
01:30:30.880 --> 01:30:33.260
Don't run. We are your friends.

910
01:30:46.850 --> 01:30:48.980
Next stop. radio station.

911
01:30:51.520 --> 01:30:53.360
There it is.

912
01:30:53.690 --> 01:30:55.110
Let's move it!

913
01:31:13.130 --> 01:31:14.750
Here it is.

914
01:31:15.880 --> 01:31:17.720
Go get it started.
Barbara. go with him.

915
01:31:17.880 --> 01:31:20.050
-Okay.
-Cindy. come with me.

916
01:31:35.440 --> 01:31:38.320
Tom. Are you sure you can fly this?

917
01:31:38.490 --> 01:31:40.570
Yeah. l think so. yeah.

918
01:31:43.120 --> 01:31:44.490
Who put that on?

919
01:31:45.410 --> 01:31:48.500
-lt's stuck.
-Cindy. over here.

920
01:31:55.000 --> 01:31:56.800
Shit.

921
01:31:56.960 --> 01:31:59.130
They haven't seen us yet. Come here.

922
01:32:00.050 --> 01:32:02.840
-Cindy. Get in the plane.
-What?

923
01:32:03.010 --> 01:32:04.800
l'm staying. l'll distract them.

924
01:32:04.970 --> 01:32:07.180
The first chance you get. you take off.

925
01:32:07.350 --> 01:32:09.850
-l'm not leaving you.
-Just do it.

926
01:32:10.020 --> 01:32:11.600
l'll draw them away. Now. go.

927
01:32:11.770 --> 01:32:14.440
-No.
-l said. go!

928
01:32:19.450 --> 01:32:21.030
Oh. my God.

929
01:32:21.950 --> 01:32:24.070
-What's he doing?
-He must have flipped!

930
01:32:24.240 --> 01:32:27.290
-He's going to throw them off.
-Yeah. but we can't leave him.

931
01:32:30.870 --> 01:32:34.290
No weapon. No clown outfit.

932
01:32:34.460 --> 01:32:36.290
Just me!

933
01:32:36.460 --> 01:32:38.460
Byron Williams...

934
01:32:38.630 --> 01:32:40.670
...heavyweight champion...

935
01:32:41.470 --> 01:32:43.130
...of the world.

936
01:33:53.910 --> 01:33:55.960
Something's happened.

937
01:33:56.130 --> 01:33:58.210
Something's happened to Byron.

938
01:34:15.020 --> 01:34:17.850
When l'm calling you

939
01:34:27.950 --> 01:34:30.080
Will you answer too

940
01:34:39.090 --> 01:34:43.920
That means l offer my love

941
01:35:02.780 --> 01:35:06.070
Our love will come true

942
01:35:08.990 --> 01:35:12.080
You belong to me

943
01:35:12.240 --> 01:35:18.620
l belong to you

944
01:35:20.630 --> 01:35:23.880
Goodbye. my darling.
l wish things could've been different.

945
01:35:24.050 --> 01:35:25.590
So do l.

946
01:35:31.300 --> 01:35:32.800
Goodbye.

947
01:35:32.970 --> 01:35:36.430
-l love you.
-l love you too. Nathalie.

948
01:37:11.950 --> 01:37:13.360
Florence Norris...

949
01:37:13.530 --> 01:37:16.530
...l hereby present to you
the Congressional Medal of Honor...

950
01:37:16.700 --> 01:37:19.080
...the highest decoration
our nation can bestow.

951
01:37:21.080 --> 01:37:24.540
Thank you. honey.
But don't you dare let this happen again.

952
01:37:26.130 --> 01:37:27.840
Richard Norris...

953
01:37:28.000 --> 01:37:31.210
...on behalf of my parents.
who couldn't be here today...

954
01:37:31.380 --> 01:37:33.590
...for saving the world
from the Martians...

955
01:37:33.760 --> 01:37:36.590
...l proudly present to you
the Medal of Honor.

956
01:37:36.760 --> 01:37:38.930
You don't have to kiss me
if you don't want to.

957
01:37:39.720 --> 01:37:41.520
l have to.

958
01:37:44.230 --> 01:37:46.480
l prepared a speech. ls that all right?

959
01:37:47.570 --> 01:37:49.320
Sure. that's very appropriate.

960
01:37:54.200 --> 01:37:56.070
Hi. everybody.

961
01:37:56.910 --> 01:37:58.280
First. l just want to say--

962
01:37:58.450 --> 01:38:01.290
Can you speak up? We can't hear you.

963
01:38:01.450 --> 01:38:04.620
Well. l want to say that there's
a lot of people in the world...

964
01:38:04.790 --> 01:38:07.250
...that have. like.
done a lot more than l have...

965
01:38:07.420 --> 01:38:12.300
...and they're the ones
that should be here now getting a medal.

966
01:38:13.630 --> 01:38:18.220
And l want to thank my grandma
for always being so good to me...

967
01:38:18.390 --> 01:38:22.270
...and for helping save the world
and everything.

968
01:38:22.430 --> 01:38:25.810
So l guess. like. now we just have to...

969
01:38:25.980 --> 01:38:29.980
...start over and start rebuilding everything.
like our houses.

970
01:38:30.150 --> 01:38:33.900
But l was thinking. maybe instead
of houses. we could live in tepees...

971
01:38:34.070 --> 01:38:37.820
...because it's better in a lot of ways.

972
01:38:41.290 --> 01:38:44.290
Okay. that's all l have to say. Thanks.

973
01:38:46.000 --> 01:38:48.880
-Was that okay?
-Yeah.

974
01:38:49.040 --> 01:38:50.790
Do you got a girlfriend?

975
01:38:50.960 --> 01:38:52.550
No.

976
01:38:53.300 --> 01:38:56.800
Guys. come on. Give me a break.
Go on in there and start cleaning your room.

977
01:38:56.970 --> 01:39:00.010
l can't do all this by myself.
Please? Look at you.

978
01:40:17.670 --> 01:40:18.720
Yeah.

